Package pt.uc.dei.entities

Class TemporaryUserEntity

java.lang.Object
pt.uc.dei.entities.TemporaryUserEntity
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
@Entity public class TemporaryUserEntity extends Object implements Serializable
Represents a temporary user account during registration process.

Stores unverified user credentials until email activation is completed. Automatically cleaned up after successful activation or expiration.

  • Field Details

    • id

      private Long id
      Unique database identifier for the temporary account. Auto-incremented by the database.

    • email

      private String email
      User's email address for account verification.

      Maximum length of 254 characters (RFC 5321 compliant). Marked as unique to prevent duplicate registrations.

    • password

      private String password
      Encrypted password for the temporary account.

      Should be hashed using secure algorithm before storage.

    • secretKey

      private String secretKey

    • activationToken

      private ActivationTokenEntity activationToken
      Activation token associated with this temporary account.

      Features: - Bi-directional one-to-one mapping - Automatic cascade operations - Orphan removal when temporary user is deleted
